nge affected by superconductivity. At larger $\\Omega$, up to\nfrequencies above the Fermi energy, $\\sigma'(\\Omega)$ scales as $1/\\Omega$,\nwhich is reminiscent of the behavior observed in the superconducting cuprates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 Jan 2014 18:11:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-18"}
